          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "TAGD",
                  "POLPS"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The polarized photon beam was generated",
                " at process of coherent bremsstrahlung of electrons in",
                " a diamond crystal.",
                "The crystal was orientated in such a way that main",
                " contribution to the coherent bremsstrahlung cross",
                " section gave one vector of the reciprocal lattice of",
                " the crystal, [0-22] for parallel and [0-2-2] for",
                " perpendicular directions of the polarization to the",
                " reaction plane."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " CD2 plate (1 mm thick), and CH2 target (1.1 mm thick)",
                "  for the carbon disintegration background subtraction.",
                " The targets were positioned on the distance ~2 m from",
                "  the photon collimator at angle 60 deg to the photon",
                "  beam direction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "CSICR",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Protons were detected by a CsI/SSD",
                " telescope placed under angle theta(p)= 90 deg to the",
                " beam axis.",
                "It consisted of two identical single-sided Si strip",
                " detectors and a CsI(Tl) counter, which functioned as",
                " delta E and E detectors, respectively.",
                "The SSDs had a thickness of 0.5 mm and 64 strips,",
                " which were paralleled in groups of two for the",
                " read-out, thus yielding an effective strip width of",
                " 2 mm.",
                "The CsI(Tl) detector was of cylinder shape of 12.5 cm",
                " in diameter and 10 cm long. Its angular acceptance",
                " (+/-14 deg FWHM) was determined by Monte Carlo",
                " simulation using the GEANT-4 package.",
                "The proton detection threshold was Eth=18 MeV that",
                " corresponded to the photon energy of Eg=40 MeV for",
                " the d(g,p)n reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
